description:
REQUIREMENTS

Candidates with 1-2 years working experience from any industries and or potential FRESH GRADS who are interesting in FINANCIAL FIELDS are considered;
Skillful knowledge in Excel;
Willing to learn and to do attitude, sedate under pressure, ATTENTIVE, reliable, and self-disciplined;
9.5 hours daily SHIFT between 08:00-23:30 required, Mondays to Fridays only.
Public Holidays SHIFT required with compensation.
NO NEED TO WORK OVERTIME.

JOB DESCRIPTION

To consolidate and settle clients’ account info to internal departments;
To sort and e-file clients’ account data;
NON-SALES role, no outbound duties required. 

We offer attractive benefits and remuneration package including first-tier working environment, 13 months salary, free lunch, performance and discretionary bonus, 5 day work, full medical and dental insurance coverage scheme, prospective career promotion, education allowance, birthday allowance, free overseas sight-seeing trip etc. Interested parities please send your CV with current and expected salary by clicking “APPLY NOW”.

Responsibilities 
Assist Manager in leading and managing a team of CSOs in delivering quality service to internal & external customers;
Introduce best practices to enhance customer experience and satisfaction, drive and track service quality on service-related initiatives;
Conduct field coaching and call quality assessments to ensure daily operations are in compliance with company & department standards;
Participate to review current processes and procedures, liaise and co-ordinate with cross-functional teams leader on continued improvement of fulfillment tasks;
Provide second line phone and email supporting to the team, ensure to meet key performance indicator (KPI) targets as set by management;
Provide premier service to difficult people, be tactful and assertive with professional sense in tackling customer requirements or complaints.
Requirements 
Degree holder or equivalent with 4 years experience in customer service and call centre environment;
1-2 years experience in supervisory level of which in e-Commerce is highly preferred;
Knowledge in developing of a call centre operations, workflow and procedure preferable;
Proficient in PC applications including MS Words, Excel and Chinese word processing, good writing and presentation skills is an advantage;
Good command of spoken and written Chinese and English, proficient in Mandarin speaking is a must;
Customer centric and attention to detail, precise and thorough; able to manage a range of tasks, people and projects;
Excellent supervisory skills with problem-solving capability and result-oriented potential;
To work on shifts, weekends and public holiday.

We offer

5 - day work week
Medical Benefits
Annual Merit Bonus
Staff Purchase Discounts
Staff Recreation Activity
Shuttle Bus Service
Education Sponsorship

Interested parties please send a full resume with current and expected salary by clicking APPLY NOW:

Human Resources Department
Sa Sa Cosmetic Co Ltd
14/F, Block B, MP Industrial Centre
18 Ka Yip Street
Chai Wan
Hong Kong

Please visit our corporate website at http://corp.sasa.com/en/home to know more about us.

(Sa Sa is an Equal Opportunity Employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment. Personal data collected will be kept confidential and used for recruitment purpose only)

Job Description

Handles customer inquiries from different incoming channels in timely manner in effective communication e.g. phone, email, digital media etc;
Manages and resolves customer complaints and assist escalated complex cases;
Provides immediate support to team members when they encounter difficulties in handling inquiries;
Performs ad hoc tasks as required by supervisor being a team player to back up other functions for service continuity;
Requirements:

At least 1 years of customer service and/or digital retail and/or digital entertainment industry experience, Fresh graduate will also be considered;
Detailed-minded, well-organized, independent, responsible, multi-tasking, ability to work under pressure and with tight deadlines;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills and ability to collaborate with different organizations and teams;
Proficiency in using Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook) & Chinese typing;
Work in Wong Chuk Hang;
